{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YLuamjHHYBdZXEXtGVVFNg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the API. Let me look at how the encode/decode works to write a proper harness:\n\n1. The harness will:\n   - Take fuzz input as a binary property list blob\n   - Call H5Pdecode() to decode it into a property list\n   - If decode succeeds, probe the decoded property list:\n     - Check nfilters with H5Pget_nfilters\n     - Iterate over filters with H5Pget_filter2\n     - Re-encode with H5Pencode2 and verify round-trip\n   - Close the property list with H5Pclose\n   - Suppress HDF5 error messages to reduce noise\n\nThe main attack surface is in the H5Pdecode parsing logic, so I'll focus the fuzzer on feeding it malformed binary blobs and checking how it handles the decode, probe, and re-encode cycle.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":470,"cache_read_input_tokens":31485,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":470,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"07c75857-1e3d-4896-b83d-7b151dc47070","uuid":"2911df93-530e-4ecb-be7e-5bbdedeadeba"}
