{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WwVy3pDk8HwjZehJt1gv5B","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build is green. Here's what the harness does:\n\n**`h5_plist_encode_decode_fuzzer`** targets the property-list binary parser directly:\n\n1. **`H5Pdecode(data)`** — feeds raw fuzzer bytes as the encoded blob. This is the primary attack surface: any length, any content is a valid test case. Failure is handled gracefully.\n2. **`H5Pencode2(plist_id, NULL, &size, H5P_DEFAULT)`** — size query, then fill — exercises the encoder on whatever the decoder produced, covering round-trip consistency bugs.\n3. **`H5Pget_nfilters` + `H5Pget_filter2` loop** — probes every filter in the pipeline when the decoded plist is a filter-bearing class (DCPL/GCPL/OCPL). `cd_nelmts` is correctly initialized to `MAX_CD_NELMTS` before each call, per the API contract.\n4. **`H5Pclose`** — always called on success to avoid leaks.\n\nAPI contracts honored: `cd_nelmts` initialized before each `H5Pget_filter2`, name buffer sized to `namelen`, filter loop guarded on `nfilters > 0`, `fapl_id = H5P_DEFAULT` (documented valid)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":150,"cache_read_input_tokens":36768,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":150,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"07c75857-1e3d-4896-b83d-7b151dc47070","uuid":"c7d7ab63-86cd-4a60-b0ae-29ef9b3ecf43"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":810252,"duration_api_ms":102044,"num_turns":26,"result":"Build is green. Here's what the harness does:\n\n**`h5_plist_encode_decode_fuzzer`** targets the property-list binary parser directly:\n\n1. **`H5Pdecode(data)`** — feeds raw fuzzer bytes as the encoded blob. This is the primary attack surface: any length, any content is a valid test case. Failure is handled gracefully.\n2. **`H5Pencode2(plist_id, NULL, &size, H5P_DEFAULT)`** — size query, then fill — exercises the encoder on whatever the decoder produced, covering round-trip consistency bugs.\n3. **`H5Pget_nfilters` + `H5Pget_filter2` loop** — probes every filter in the pipeline when the decoded plist is a filter-bearing class (DCPL/GCPL/OCPL). `cd_nelmts` is correctly initialized to `MAX_CD_NELMTS` before each call, per the API contract.\n4. **`H5Pclose`** — always called on success to avoid leaks.\n\nAPI contracts honored: `cd_nelmts` initialized before each `H5Pget_filter2`, name buffer sized to `namelen`, filter loop guarded on `nfilters > 0`, `fapl_id = H5P_DEFAULT` (documented valid).","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"07c75857-1e3d-4896-b83d-7b151dc47070","total_cost_usd":0.33376425000000004,"usage":{"input_tokens":22,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16571,"cache_read_input_tokens":633640,"output_tokens":5431,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16571},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":22,"outputTokens":5431,"cacheReadInputTokens":633640,"cacheCreationInputTokens":16571,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.33376425000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"bd8d182a-4c83-461e-b21c-2dde919f6b74"}
